</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="430" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="25.[813,1277,1874,1898]" box="[813,1277,1874,1898]" pageId="25" pageNumber="430">
DISTRIBUTION. — Endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[1118,1274,1874,1898]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="25" pageNumber="430">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[813,1457,1922,2025]" pageId="25" pageNumber="430">
HABITAT. — 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chopard" authorityYear="1915" box="[946,1055,1922,1946]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Notosciobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[946,1055,1922,1946]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="430">Notosciobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species live in forested area, where they are encountered in leaf litter; they are often found in burrows; one juvenile has been found in a gallery under a small stone together with a scorpion (LDG and JA, pers. obs.).
</paragraph>
